fields.name: Touché Hombre
fields.information:
Tacos and Tequila from Mexico with a Melbourne twist. Killing it since 2012.

Reviews from Zomato:

Came here the other day at 4.30pm on a weekday. Barely anyone there as obviously not peak time. Got rejected because we only wanted cocktails and not food. This is a restaurant not a bar, you need to eat is what we were told. Sorry but when you're charging the price of a first born for cocktails and your restaurants empty, isn't any money good money? We went elsewhere and wont be coming back. A shame as we have eaten here many times prior.

Love my Mexican and expected great things! Touché hombre offers really down to earth and first rate friendly service but it's bloody expensive for what you get. The food is tasty but some dishes felt like they were dripping in grease and portion sizes are varied and overly complex for my simple pallet. Wine list ok but nothing special, ambience offers a funky and intimate vibe, maybe a little too chain Mexican if you follow (thought I spied a waiter in a poncho and sombrero 😉) but definitely worth a look for a convenient and fun night out within arms reach of city nightlife.

Can not fault. We were seated without wait on a Saturday night (lucky - there were no other free tables). Cocktails were creative, strong & delicious. Corn was amazing!!! And the tacos were fab too. Customer service was above & beyond - the waitress gave us excellent information and recommendations as to a post dinner tequila shot. The music was fun too! Cannot wait to come back!

fields.name: Operator25
fields.information:
The very first use of the building back in the early 1900's was Melbourne's first switchboard, hence the name. The cobblestone wall adorns the heritage listed facade, concealing a modern rustic ambience inside. 

Whether you're a party of many or an intimate catchup with friends, Operator25 has a space for you. We are kids friendly and welcome the solo grazer flicking through the day's news.

The approach to food at Operator25 is to use seasonal produce with classic flavours and other combinations that we know are comfort food, but with a little bit of a twist.

And we serve specialty coffee using the finest beans from Melbourne’s own Code Black Coffee roaster. Whether you're a fan of espresso based, aeropress, pour over or cold drip coffee, we've got you covered. 

Reviews from Zomato:

 Its a little specialty-coffee-brunch located very close to flagstaff garden. I had the teriyaki benedict and a cup of magic. The food is outstanding, all of the components are meaningful and add a little bit of everything to the plate. It's so mouth-gratifying and the coffee itself is just as good as the food! Will definitely be coming back to try their other menus ""

Interior was very unique along with the menu however beyond this instagrammable aesthetic, the dishes themselves were nothing short of mediocre. I ordered the matcha waffles which was lacking flavour overall and was not enjoyable, however did look very appealing. The ambiance was relaxed and quiet as it was a weekday.

This is a gem of a Vegan place! Not overly trendy, just small and low fuss which suits it. 
I can never go past the Madras, warning-hot, but all the dishes that come out look great 

Super friendly staff. 

Place is now a favourite of ours!

"" I would say food was okay since you cant find any vegetarian thai restaurants. The portion was small so we had to order a few extra to shre. Had the green curry, basil stir fry tofu, tom yum soup, massaman curry, prawn salad and crispy saltpeper tofu. They dont have thai milk tea which is bizarre. Found ants in my tom yum soup , sent it back and the waitress asked if it was crawling on the table as it wasnt from their kitchen - how not helpful!

Wife took me and the kiddo here for my birthday - I am so happy we went there. We ordered Steam Wantons for entree, a green curry and a nasi goreng and a vegetarian japanese curry: The food was very good! The creativity and simplicity of the food left me feeling very happy we went there and this was one of the best asian-vegetarian we have been to. We didn't go there because we wanted to taste (vege) lamb or chicken! We went there purely for the vegetarian asian they had to offer and we absolutely loved it.

Will go again and strongly recommended.

The best tom yum around!!! I get the tom yum soup almost every time! It's a small portion (but perfect size for me!). I've also had the Thai 'lamb' curry, the mock meat looked and tasted like real meat so it kinda freaked me out (I am vegan) but the flavours were great!

Reviews from Zomato:

I have been here a couple of times for lunch just because it's close to my work place and have decent tasting thai food, but never been impressed. The quantity of stirfry is meagre and really disappointing. I literally had to struggle to save enough stirfry to finish my rice with. The quantity of protein (chicken or meat is way too less) never been to a restaurant that is so miserly with food. The set up is good though, overall an average place.

Thai cuisine was on the Swine's hit list today. Thailander was the Swine's stop for a quick feed. First time here for the Swine. The Little Collins St outlet is tiny but has a few share tables for customers to eat in. Luckily the Swine squad got to sit and eat. The Swine ordered a regular Beef Mossoman Curry - a fave! Despite appearing like a very small serving it was actually plentiful for the Swine's big guts. Taste was also better than expected - authentic. The menu does have most of the usual culprits when it comes to Thai food - pad thai, rice, red and green curries, to name a few bad boys n girls. There was a bit of a wait for food, which was the main sore point (but it was peak hour). Nothing essential but not terrible either. The Swine would go again.
 Thailander, CBD Photos

The price is very reasonable for the food they have. But it's what you get. Not bad, but nothing special. Cannot say the service was very good since I didn't see a smile, but it was okay, they have take out boxes and gave a bit more fingers when asked. Good to go for a quick take out or a lunch special.

fields.name: The Meatball Bar - Leederville
fields.information:
The Meatball Bar in Leederville is located within the thriving culture of the City of Vincent. Launched in 2015 and now licensed to serve alcohol, it caters for those who are wanting a relaxed environment to enjoy great food and a great range of alcoholic beverages.

The Meatball Bar is a place you need to pocket swiftly, with regulars from the so-called Ballers Club laying their hands on tables as if they were Faberge eggs, reason being chiefly the well-rounded menu.
The handsome pair of Meatball Bars was whipped into shape by enterprising restaurateur and culinary all-rounder Giovanni Pezzano, keen to show off his intuition that the Italian meatball, provided it was massaged into being from premium grade meats and carefully selected flavours, could surpass any dry-aged grain-fed Wagyu steak bosh touted from restaurant menu to restaurant menu the length of the land. Here, everyone of the wide-ranging international cuisines available to the kitchen is served as a ball, ensuring (and we quote) that every guest enjoys a mouthful of exceptional flavours. 
 Leederville! Append balls to any of the following international falvours: deep-fried bocconcini cheese with cashew and basil pesto for a real Italian kick, Malaysian peanut satay chicken and pork or red Thai curry beef with kaffir lime, caramelised papaya and toasted coconut to pay homage to Australian cuisine’s deep rootedness in Asian culinary traditions. Going further, bigger billiards listed under ‘Sexy Balls’ include the traditional Italian breed, Middle eastern pumpkin with Jersey feta, and sundry balls featuring the flesh of bull, pig, chicken, lamb and bull, including the tantalising pulled beef with sour cream and then some.

fields.name: Fo Guang Yuan Art Gallery
fields.information:
Reviews from Zomato:

The food was absolutely spot on and well flavoured despite being very simple. I'm so impressed by how cheap it is as well, only costing my friend and I $32 in total as we shared an entree and two mains! Would definitely come back! Not to mention the service was relatively good, and we were served very quickly!

It was a very great experience for me and my friend when we ate here. I ordered the veg steak with mushroom gravy and a side of rice, and was pleasantly surprised that it came with extras, such as potato cakes, extra veggies and even a bite-sized jelly.  Me and my friend also shared some veggie mushroom buns as well as a pot of lotus tea which we also really enjoyed. 

As for the atmosphere, it's definitely one that is unique and quaint from other restaurants so it's quite refreshing in that sense, also very therapeutic as they play oriental music in the background. The prices are reasonable, the staff friendly, and me and my friend thoroughly enjoyed everything else the place had to offer, such as the gallery and the prayer room, so we both definitely intend to come back!

A surprisingly pleasant visit to this place for a quick lunch. One might walk right past this place, not knowing the peaceful hidden dining hall inside. Great variety of vegetarian food. Service is good and fast. Ordered their kumquat tea which is delightful and tried out their new lunch box special of the day, vegetarian Teriyaki chicken with crispy tofu. Both the chicken and crispy tofu were great. Give it a go if you're nearby.

fields.name: Nene Chicken
fields.information: The name “NeNe” simply means “Yes! Yes!” in Korean. They pride ourselves on delivering the NeNe experience with our farm-fresh poultry and produce together with our tireless quality service and a happy dining experience.

fields.name: Vans Cafe
fields.information: VANS has evolved as your favourite local coffee shop. Relaxed without compromising attention to detail we are open for breakfast, lunch and dinner.

fields.name: Park & Vine
fields.address: 31 Gayton Road, City Beach, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Weekend brunches are a good place to start at Park & Vine. It’s a comfortable bar and restaurant, best accessed from Gayton Road, and there’s everything from eggs as you like them on sourdough for the bare-bones bruncher to luxurious trout gravlax, pork belly bacon on potato pancakes, fantastic Asian-Middle Eastern fusion in the pork kofta bao buns – it’s eminently modern Australian, and a very welcome addition to the Perth casual dining. scene. 
Lunch and dinner sees the kitchen at Park & Vine pulling out all the stops for a smorgasbord of dishes that toe the line between casual and affordable and five-star Australian cuisine. The chef’s tasting board is a daily delight that comes highly recommended for those diners that like a tasty surprise, while the massive tomahawk steak special (with cheesy duck-fat potatoes and a red wine jus) comfortably feeds two to three people. When truffles in season, you can get the rare delicacy shaved onto any dish for a tenner, bringing extra fruity pungency to the yabbie and sweetcorn ravioli, the house Park & Vine burger, cured Ranger Valley beef salad, vegetarian polenta, or the slow-cooked and smoked BBQ beef brisket with chargrilled corn, Cajun butter and Texas-style sauce. Bookings essential for this gem hidden away in Perth’s City Beach.

fields.name: Cecchi's
fields.information: Cecchi's restaurant opened in late 2012. Started by Mark Cecchi and wife Kylee-Anne, Cecchi's brings the value of homeliness and European heritage together to create the warmth of walking into a friend's dining room mixed with the culinary excitement of fine dining. Restaurant photo credit: instagram.com/morsels_perth

fields.name: Kava Cafe

fields.name: Chi Restaurant
fields.address: Shop 14, 366 Albany Highway, Victoria Park, Perth, WA
fields.information:
a Southern Chinese cuisine specialist with premium trappings, but if you haven’t yet experienced dining at Chi, now’s your chance to book some of the city’s most coveted tables. Standing head and shoulders above the competition, Chi’s Victoria Park premises – easily accessed along the Albany Highway – are designed to cater to diners with a taste for refinement. In the kitchen, artful East and Central Asian culinary techniques combine with fresh Western Australian produce to create signature delicacies like the range of ‘Breath of the Wok’ dishes that are along a major drawcard. 
Chi’s award-winning selection of Chinese specialties include dishes that must be pre-ordered (simply leave a note when you reserve online), something that already underscores Chi’s reputation as a truly gourmet Chinese restaurant in Perth. Live lobster, snow and mud crab and two-style whole fish are on the cards at market price, subject to seasonal availability, while the eight treasure whole duck, slow-cooked pork hock, and classic Peking duck served over three courses are legendary meat dishes. Also popular at Chi’s Victoria Park restaurant are the mouthwatering, brothy Chinese hotpots packed with basil chicken, beef brisket, roast pork belly, Chinese sausages and more, or the huge selection of seafood main courses. Topping many a food critics’ annual list, we shouldn’t have to remind diners that advance online bookings for tables at Chi Restaurant’s Albany Highway address are strongly advised!

fields.name: Little Shop of Plenty
fields.information: Plenty is a little business in Perth, Western Australia with the goal of helping folks to achieve better health simply by eating better food.  A big part of this is realising that a healthy, plant based diet doesn't mean starving on nothing but bowls of lettuce (all due respect to lettuce!)  There are plenty of satisfying plant based dishes to be tried which contain plenty of protein, plenty of minerals - iron & calcium included – and plenty of exciting flavours to keep us coming back for more!!

fields.name: Vegie Bar
fields.information:
Opened 20 year ago, with the original ideals of offering somewhere healthy to eat, Vegie Bar's basic ideals have remained-food for the body, mind and soul. Today Vegie Bar continues to flourish offering tasty food that's healthy and affordable in a fun and relaxed environment. Not limited to the vegetarian, the popular eating house and bar entices a wide mix of people and has become an iconic destination in Melbourne.

The food and drinks menu offers a huge variety of freshly prepared, dishes from all corners of the globe. Wherever possible organic and bio-dynamic ingredients are used .This reflects another belief-that the food should not be over-worked and should have minimal human involvement throughout the preparation and cooking stages, resulting in rustic, home-style cooking.

From humble beginnings over 20 years ago, Vegie Bar has grown to become one of Melbourne’s most popular haunts for both the health conscious and the hungry. Serving a vast array of dishes inspired by the world over, Vegie Bar continues to treat the masses to delicious and accessible contemporary vegetarian cooking.

We came here for the first time for the kbbq, and it's definitely worth to try! We also had a few items from their sushi menu and it was so delicious and fresh! Will definitely come back for the sushi train next time!

fields.name: Wagyu One
fields.information: Wagyu One is the Wagyu Beef professional, in the city centre of Melbourne, Australia. Wagyu One has Wagyu specialists to consult our preparation and sauces for meats.

fields.name: No35
fields.address: Sofitel Melbourne On Collins, Level 35, 25 Collins Street, CBD, Melbourne
fields.information:
Located on level 35 of Sofitel Melbourne On Collins is the hotel’s signature restaurant, No35. This sophisticated dining destination is elegantly designed with rich timbers, vibrant tones, contemporary artworks and features breathtaking views of Melbourne.
Open 7 days for breakfast and dinner, with lunch service on select days, the restaurant serves contemporary cuisine with innovative flair. It specialises in using fresh, regional produce to create unique dishes with clean and pure flavours. These dishes are matched with an outstanding wine selection and attentive service that greets you upon arrival.

Reviews from Zomato:

Went here for my dad's 50th with my family. Such a lovely, classy venue with delicious food to match. I had the lamb with roast veggies and a yummy jus. Will definitely be returning!

Seafood plate really yummy and fresh,bigger size prawn so UMAMI,I'm a seafood fans so that is not enough for me.
Slow cook lamb for 2 person,be honestly We didn't finish it,big serve of lamb.
Their a lot of wine from yarra velly,We were taste Pinot noir
It is normal price and was ok,maybe view and service took my focus,haha!!anyway that's good place for dating,
So relaxing! We will come back.

Creme brûlée with raspberry coulee was amazing, perfectly well balanced and the raspberry added a tartness to the brûlée. There was a loud tapping sound. Wait for desserts was quite a while but it was worth it, around 20 minutes but understandable because it was made from freshly

Had a fab birthday dinner here, food was good & views were amazing. It wouldn't be my first choice for a foodie dinner but a great location for a fancy experience!

fields.name: Hylin
fields.address: 178 Railway Parade, West Leederville, Leederville, Perth, WA
fields.information: Hylin is an intimate neighbourhood cafe. Located in West Leederville, this architecturally designed space offers a contemporary outlook, great coffee and mouth watering eats. Come in and say Hello!

fields.name: Marroo Korean Charcoal BBQ & Bar
fields.information: Established on the 15th February 2013, Marroo is the hottest Korean BBQ place in the city. Fully licensed and open until late 7 days a week and on public holidays and weekends it is bound to impress.

fields.name: Duende
fields.information: Everyday for Everyone. Breakfast till 12pm Friday Saturday and Sunday, coffee, tapas, restaurant, cheese, desserts, wine & cocktail bar.

fields.name: Holly Raye's
fields.information: Look for the little white building just off Old Perth Road with the big Angus dog painted on the side. Baked goods, yummy breakfast and delicious coffee

fields.name: James Parker Sushi X Sake
fields.address: Shop 2 182 James St, Northbridge, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Inspired by Japanese traditional dining-style, James Parker offers the finest Japanese delicacies in a great and unique atmosphere. Our menu offers a great selection of Japanese dishes and drinks using the freshest ingredients and are designed to be shared and served steadily as you dine. 
Restaurant photo credit: dumplinglove.wordpress.com

fields.name: Transformer
fields.information:
Reviews from Zomato:

It's an experience for all senses! The atmosphere is completely different at night than during the day, but always cozy, entertaining and intimate. The waiters are all welcoming and accomodating. Have had an all vegan, gluten free, fructose friendly feast here a few times and everything never fails to impress! The chocolate cake that they are able to provide for birthdays is fantastic and I had no difficulties gobbling it all up even after the lengthy 'Feed Me' menu. The 'Grilled King Oyster Mushrooms', 'Roasted Sweet Potato', and 'Roast Cauliflower with saffron yoghurt' are among my favourite. The 'Bowl of Mork Ganache Hot Chocolate' is a real treat, as well as all their vegan desserts. If you haven't yet been, you need to get your ass over there for a unique and terrific taste experience.

Came here for a vegetarian friends birthday on a Saturday night. We opted for the 'Feed me' menu & whoa!! It was delicious, so much really good food & a good taste of everything. My favorite was the eggplant at the end. We also enjoyed a few cocktails & mocktails. The decor was really lovely & a good vibe to it. Staff were really nice.

Fantastic impression when you first walk in, amazing Fitbit and quick friendly welcome, tempting menu too. All of the dishes we ordered seemed to be lacking something that would make them otherwise faultless, perhaps more salt? As with a lot of other reviews, small portion sizes or incredibly overpriced for what it is.

fields.name: Siena's of Leederville
fields.information:
Their menu is packed with Italian favourites, from authentic pizzas to pastas, risottos and their house signature parmigianas, which can be topped with the likes of mozzarella, tomatoes, eggplant or feta. 
Siena’s have all the antipasti starters that we know and love: bruschetta, calamari, garlic bread, chilli prawns, mozzarella croquettes and plenty more, as well as Minestrone soup and a huge range of salads. Once you’ve had your fill there then you can move on to the star of the show: the pizza. Alongside the classics – margherita, pepperoni, vegetarian – there are more expansive and authentic options such as Calabrese, with ricotta, grilled eggplant and oregano, Jojo, with Italian sausage and leg ham and the extra special Salmone, on a tomato-free base and featuring salmon, brie, mozzarella and basil. Throw in a selection of parmigianas, an Italian gelato list and a wine list as long as your arm and you’re well on the way to a big night out in Perth. Book a table today and set a course for Oxford Street in Leederville for an Italian feast at Siena’s.

fields.name: Mason & Bird
fields.information: The menu offers all day brunch in the form of burgers, toasties, paleo waffles, housemade cocoa pops and some serious contenders in the pasta department.

fields.name: Good Fortune Roast Duck House
fields.information: Good Fortune was founded by Mr. Jin Shou Chen in 1999. Mr Chen has over 20 years of experience in the food industry, specializing in roast duck, as well as the classic BBQ pork, roast pork and BBQ pork ribs. Roast Duck, or Peking Duck is a famous duck dish from Beijing that has been prepared since the imperial era. Peking Duck is considered one of China's national foods. We pride ourselves in serving quality roast ducks using traditional recipes and hygiene methods.

fields.name: Chapas
fields.address: 634 Beaufort Street, Mount Lawley, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Flavoursome and juicy, and the bun was so soft. The dumplings were interesting but equally tasty. The fried rice was very good, not too oily and had the perfect combination of flavour --Foodieperth Expert in Mount Lawley

Best Chinese restaurant in Perth! I'm celiac, so they have A LOT of gluten free meals options! The food is amazing, so teasty!Service is excellent --Valentina A.

Fantastic place. Great food, amazing hospitality, and such consideration for my coeliac daughter who polished off a serving of your squid tentacles almost by herself. We will definitely be back. --Amanda G.

fields.name: Raw Trader
fields.information: Raw Trader is a café specialising in organic, raw, vegan, vegetarian, paleo, gluten free, dairy free and sugar free healthy desserts and treats.

fields.name: Shimbashi Soba & Sake Bar
fields.information:
We opened the restaurant in June 2012 to bring to Melbourne the wholesome deliciousness of Soba (buckwheat noodles) and traditional Japanese cuisine. We use Tasmanian buckwheat groats (which are also exported to Japan) to make our own stone-milled buckwheat flour, and use that to make our hand-kneaded noodles.

Reviews from Zomato:

Great Japanese food, I love how they make their own soba. I've had the soba with the duck so many times, the broth is delicious and the duck is cooked really well. Would also recommend the Gyoza! 

Went here with a few friends, the place doesn't take bookings and is fairly busy. We had the okonomiyaki to share, it was very tasty. My friends ordered the salmon soba salad, this is served with cold soba and I really like the taste after having a taste. I ordered the warm natto soba with rice cake. The natto (fermented soy beans) taste is quite strong and a little bitter. The soba is handmade and has a nice texture eaten cold, I'll probably come back for cold soba next time as the texture is not the same eaten warm.

Soba soba soba. Best soba I've found since being in Japan. They even grind the buckwheat in the restaurant! Loads of Japanese drinks available and prices weren't too bad either. Great little lunch spot in the city, and awesome for hot days as they have cold soba salads.

This is definitely a 'must try' Japanese restaurant. It's quaint and authentic in atmosphere which impressed us from the get go. The food was very good and the service too. Really enjoyed it overall.

fields.name: The Attic Fremantle
fields.information: Walk-Ins Welcome and Good For Kids.

fields.name: Pearfect Pantry
fields.information: Vegan Big Mac. Vegan cupcakes. & many more vegan &knob vegan options!! All made in our kitchen with passion you can taste.

fields.name: Yong Green Food
fields.information:
"Yong Green Food is a vegetarian and vegan restaurant based in Fitzroy, Melbourne. We specialise in raw, organic, vegan, gluten free, and biodynamic food and drinks.

We use organic ingredients wherever possible, subject to seasonal and market constraints, and we work with accredited organic suppliers to bring you the freshest and best ingredients. 

We have built this business with the intention of creating a better world where every living being is respected. 

We believe we are here on earth to live in harmony with nature and that there is enough food for everyone if we consciously choose what we eat. 

This philosophy is embodied in the food we serve at Yong – delicious food that nourishes and satisfies without sacrificing other lives. 

Our wholesome food not only gives the essential energy we need to sustain our body, it also serves as a means to connect us with nature. Without this connection, we cannot be whole either. 

At Yong, we serve predominantly organic vegetarian food prepared according to ying and yang principles and using eco-friendly methods as much as possible.  	

We are so grateful for being able to live our dream. 

Thank you for supporting our vision for a better world. 

You make this possible. 

Our commitment to a low-carbon future
Through Community Climate Chest, we have purchased 8.7 MWh of accredited GreenPower to be supplied to the national electricity grid to replace the energy we draw. 

We have also acquired 0.21 tonnes of carbon credits from certified abatement projects. 

This reduces our greenhouse emissions by 11.95 tCO2-e for the 12 months to March 2015. "

fields.name: Chilli Orange
fields.address: 21 Angove St, North Perth, Perth, WA
fields.information: Chilli Orange is everything that’s great about picking the boldest and best ingredients and matching them expertly in the same rice bowl. Chef Anthony Truong draws on years of culinary globetrotting to make this modern restaurant a surefire destination for curious foodies city-wide.

fields.name: Hangout on 20 Preston
fields.address: 20 Preston Street, Como, South Perth, Perth, WA
fields.information: If you want to catch up with friends over excellent barista coffee, have an intimate meal for two , meet up with the boys ( or girls) for wicked cocktails, or even enjoy a weekend breakfast, hangout on 20 Preston will provide the perfect backdrop.

fields.name: Hash Specialty Coffee
fields.information:
Our strenght: the Hash hot chocolate, presented with a beaker of rich, melted MORK chocolate and a towering cup of snow white fairy floss amidst their playful, modern take on the usual brunch options.

Reviews from Zomato:

Wow!! A great place for brunch. Food was fantastic. I had the Espresso Pannacotta and for someone that never eats vegan or gluten free- I was completely surprised at how amazing it tasted especially for a pannacotta!! My husband had the Pork Benedict and it was a great take on the classic, the pork was cooked beautifully, so tender. As a lover of Mork chocolate I knew I had to get the Hot Chocolate and it did not disappoint, was super rich chocolate just the way I like it. Well done Hash!

Heard many great things about Hash Specialty so obviously wanted to give it a go! Surprisingly not a long wait to grab a seat, after putting my name down maybe only a 5 minute wait! Service was super friendly by all staff which was lovely! Great setup inside. Ordered the Pork Benedict and Poached eggs with avo and tomatoes! Both were presented fantastically. Although the pork in the Benedict was suppose to be the star of the dish, I honestly thought it let it down and may have even been better without. I can't say why, it just tasted a bit towards the bland side. Hot chocolate was fun, very rich, couple with fairy floss and not something you will find just anywhere. All in all this place is tops!

fields.name: Bathers Beach House
fields.information: A sunny lunch by the sea, the Bather’s Beach House it could only be! A stunning location that brings the waves and the sand so close while you’re dinning in an ultra-modern and crisp establishment.

fields.name: Rabbit in the Moon
fields.address: 2 Doepel Street, North Fremantle, Fremantle, Perth, WA
fields.information: Bring friends, or bring a book. We'll serve you good coffee and treats made by our cook.

fields.name: Le Vietnam
fields.address: 80 Barrack Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Vietnamese French Cafe. Their Banh Mis are the must-try.

fields.name: Manuka Woodfire Kitchen
fields.information: We are a fully licensed restaurant, bar and alfresco serving local beer, wine, cider and coffee. Using our woodfire oven and the open flames to create simple and honest food allowing the produce to speak for itself.

fields.name: Satsuki
fields.address: Shop 1, Subiaco Square, 50 Station Street, Subiaco, Perth, WA
fields.information: Satsuki prides itself on providing a truly authentic Japanese dining experience that focuses on quality, beauty and attention to detail. Japanese dining encourages social interaction around the table, with the idea of a number of dishes to be ordered and shared.

fields.name: Source Foods
fields.information: Source Foods Cafe is commited to providing fresh & sustainable tasty home made food, coffee & juice options with minimal ecological impact. Eat and drink happy :)

fields.name: Amigos
fields.information: “Amigo” is Spanish for “Mate”, and the key ingredient to our humble family-roots Mexican-Inspired culinary destination is exactly that; mate-ship, camaraderie and family.

fields.name: Gami Chicken and Beer
fields.address: 3B Shafto Lane, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Specialising in Korean-style fried chicken, GAMI is a franchise based in Melbourne. GAMI story began in 2006 with the founder 'Rio Yoon' in Carnegie. WIth years of hands on experience with Korean cuisine, Rio decided to focus on perfecting a recipe for fried chicken & sauces, and sharing one of his country's favourite foods to the world.

fields.name: Sezar
fields.information:
Ancient as the history of Armenia itself, Armenian cuisine reflects the history and geography of this beautiful land, incorporating it with external influences. A mouth-watering array of spices and flavours combine with fresh meats, fish, vegetables and fruits to create unique flavours and aromas designed to tantalise all tastebuds.

SEZAR opened in late November 2013 by the crew behind The Black Toro in Glen Waverley. Offering a fresh and modern approach to traditional Armenian cooking techniques and flavours, SEZAR’s cuisine can be best described as New Armenian.

SEZAR’s enthusiastic and knowledgeable team are always there to ensure you have an amazing experience; they will guide you through a new style of food, inventive cocktails and a well-structured wine list. The kitchen will best accommodate for all dietary requirements including preparing gluten-free, dairy-free and vegan options if prior notice is given. Most meat dishes are prepared using halal-certified meat and while the kitchen itself is not 100% halal, utensils are strictly kept separately to avoid cross contamination.

Bookings are highly recommended, especially during Friday and Saturday evenings where two seatings have been established to cater for high demand: 5:30pm to 8:00pm and 8:30pm onwards.

Reviews from Zomato:

Amazing food! I had the set menu $40 inc drink. Great variety and even better staff. very friendly! It's very intimate with probably only 20 seats. Great date spot

Food was not as good as expected. Hospitality was good. We ordered lamb and chicken, both were not cooked upto the mark. Overall, it was ok.

fields.name: The Sporting Globe
fields.address: Rockingham Shopping Centre, 1 Syren Street, Rockingham, Perth, WA
fields.information: The Sporting Globe - Rockingham is a premium Sports Bar & Grill and the place to watch all the biggest sporting events LIVE from around the globe on over 60 HD screens. Come in to enjoy their large range of beers and ciders on tap, internationally bottled beers and cocktails.

fields.name: Good Things Cafe
fields.address: 128 Wellington Street, Mosman Park, Perth, WA
fields.information: All day breakfast menu and specialty coffee roasted by Mircology Coffee Roasters.

fields.name: Manise Cafe
fields.address: Shop 2, 449 William Street, Northbridge, Perth, WA
fields.information: Indonesians believe in giving a "kick start" to their palate with the heat of chilli and the sour crunch of pickles, so meals generally comprise of rice, sambal and pickles with small amounts of meats, seafood or vegetables, often in curry form.

fields.name: Run Amuk
fields.address: 386A South Terrace, South Fremantle, Fremantle, Perth, WA
fields.information: If a hot dog has never sent you into a state of frenzy, you’re about to experience something pretty damn special. At run amuk, we go crazy for high quality, locally made bratwurst sausages, in fact, nothing else will do. We’re talking 70% pork, 30% beef and a wild blend of herbs and spices. All meat is sourced from WA farmers and our bratwurst sausages are free from artificial colours, flavours and preservatives plus they’re gluten free.

fields.name: Teahouse at Chinatown
fields.information:
"For over a decade, Teahouse at Chinatown has elevated the standard of traditional Chinese restaurants. We are completely dedicated to procuring the finest material and treat those ingredients with uncompromising respect and sophisticated technique, expecting the balance of tastes, textures, fragrances and colors are presented in a way that enhance and accent the other.

Reviews from Zomato:

The Manager of this restaurant have attitude problem. He like to annoy people and make fun of people. It refers to the owner that work in the restaurant. His name is Shannon. With his branches at Oakleigh in Warrigal road. The manager is Thomas and Elsa. This three people are no good.

Located in the heart of China Town, Melbourne. Food is delicious here. We were with a group with varied dietary needs, lost in translation at times but all in all a good place.

Out for a quiet Sunday lunch, we found the Teahouse at Chinatown just off Little Bourke street. We were greeted with very pleasant surrounding and attentive staff. We went with the lunch banquet, and found every course to be top quality and tasteful. In fact I'd go as far to say, it was the best Chinese meal I've ever had in the CBD. 
Will definitely be returning to this restaurant.

Old school Asian lunch with the obligatory suited floor staff. We had the lunch banquet which was very good, with no real surprises or standout. Good venue for a quite business lunch. Good wine list. Has that 1980 something going on, not in a bad way.

fields.name: Noodle Forum
fields.address: Equus Arcade, Shop 203, 580 Hay Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Noodle Forum was born from a passion to create traditional handmade noodles that are fresh and full of flavour that everyone can enjoy.

fields.name: Gazi
fields.information:
Named after and inspired by an eclectic neighbourhood surrounding an old gasworks in Athens, GAZI is a Greek restaurant in Melbourne CBD where anything goes.
From the ink-splattered walls to industrial steel benches, GAZI is a no-frills, no-fuss bar-slash-Greek-restaurant where you can drink, eat and let loose – without the rules.
Want to book? You can. Booking not your thing? Just rock up.
We don’t mind what you do, as long as you get stuck into our impressive range of sensational cocktails. 
As the latest venture of renowned Greek chef and restaurateur George Calombaris, we offer a pretty impressive range of Greek food, too. 
So while you’re here, get your hands dirty with our tasty Greek street food – designed to soak up the alcohol while you soak up the fun. 
Join us and get lost in the cool and carefree atmosphere of the most eccentric neighbourhood in Greece, without leaving Melbourne’s CBD.

Reviews from Zomato:

Very enjoyable dinner for 3 people seated in a window booth. Cheese saganaki, pita with duck and onion bhaji, pork belly, fantastic Chips with feta and a roast pumpkin dish, Oh and beer and Gazi Julep cocktails. Super service and very tasty - busy due to Australian Open second week, but we enjoyed the humming atmosphere and music in the beautiful venue.

First time trying Greek food. I think it was ok but im not a fan. The place is very beautiful though. Server tried his best to explain to us about the menu but seems like in a rush. Thumbs up for the beautiful ceiling decoration.

fields.name: Davvero Caffé e Cucina
fields.address: Floreat Forum Shopping Centre, Shop R2, 1 Howtree Place, Floreat, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Davvero brings a genuine slice of Italy to Floreat diners, serving up authentic Italian favourites from classic pizzas to hearty pastas, not to mention some of the freshest meat and seafood you’ll find in any. The stylish setting combines rustic decor with modern touches, and the atmosphere is always casual and jovial in the most Italian way. Found inside the Floreat Forum Shopping Centre on Howtree Place, Davvero is a more-than-safe bet for quality Italian dining for anybody living in or visiting Perth.
Many a memorable meal here in Floreat Forum has begun with a shared antipasti board, like the Davvero Seafood board (a stew of fresh calamari, green peas, lemon & extra virgin oil anchovies, and king prawns wrapped in prosciutto), especially when you combine it with a glass of something from Davvero’s impressive Italian wine list – over 60 labels chosen from across every region in Italy.
Then you can move on to a mouthwatering main like the Guance di manzo con polenta (beef cheeks slow-cooked in Chianti red wine, served with polenta concia). However, it’s not only elegant evening dining here on Howtree Place, because Davvero are open for breakfast (freshly baked pastries are impossible to resist in the early hours, or try an Italian special like the ricotta pancakes) and lunch (a light chargrilled vegetable salad, house-made potato gnocchi, or Whiterocks veal sauteed with oyster mushrooms?). This Floreat favourite draws in aficionados of Italian cuisine from all over Perth, especially for lunch, so it’s wise to book a table and time slot well in advance.

fields.name: Stalactites Greek Restaurant
fields.information:
The delicious menu includes mouth-watering Greek dishes such as the world famous giros souvlaki, home made fresh dips, tasty grilled meats and rustic home style dishes from the Peloponnese region of Greece.

Open 24 hours, 7 days a week, Stalactites' casual and bustling atmosphere is ideal for the early bird after a hearty breakfast, families and locals out in the city and the late night owl looking for an after midnight bite to eat.

Stalactites is a favorite with the locals and a essential stop for anyone visiting Melbourne's Greek Precinct.

Reviews from Zomato:

We have been to this Greek restaurant since many years ago, and it still maintaining their quality food till today. The dipping sauce were nice! Their open souvlaki was generous. Friendly staffs and great location.

Average Greek place with average food, there are definitely other better Greek restaurants out there. (Try skewered) 
Be sure to contact them if they're open on public holidays as they can fool you that they call themselves a 24/7 Greek restaurant.
Staff can bring an attitude towards you.
Chicken pieces can get really hard and dry.
Only been twice but won't be back in a long time.
Take your lover, friends and family here to try it out.

First time having Giro at stalactites on a friday night without any expectation, but I was amazed!!! It was mind blowing!!! We ordered the pita bread and extra mixed dipping. Both lamb and chicken meat combo and they were flavoursome and tender. I wish Stalactites open just one in Perth!!! I definately will be a loyal customer.

fields.name: Izakaya Hachibeh
fields.information: A Japanese owned and operated venue on Bourke Street. Dining out in Melbourne is never a chore, and the hungry public of the city are spoilt for choice with the huge range of international culinary options that are open to them morning, noon and night.

fields.name: Babylon Cafe
fields.information: Located in the Leedervile gardens at the rear of The Rug Studio. Babylon promises coffee done right.

fields.name: Padbury's Cafe Restaurant
fields.information: Having a strong background in farming, both Michael and Helena understand the importance of using good quality fresh ingredients. With a focus on serving quality food, you can rest assured that the food you have ordered are cooked with the best ingredients available.

fields.name: Mad Dogs Jungle Bar
fields.information: Mad Dogs Jungle Bar serves awesome cocktails and 16 Australian Craft Beers on tap. Most popular dishes include Wings of the Bird and Mad Dogs Burger.

fields.name: Mandoon Estate
fields.information: Exploring the Swan River in 1827, Captain James Stirling discovered Mandoon "place of many trees" in the tongue of local aboriginies. In 1840, the Surveyor General, John Septimus Roe, established a vineyard on its fertile banks which is today the home of Mandoon Estate.

fields.name: Chin Chin
fields.information: Chin Chin Restaurant is open 11:00 AM till late, 7 days a week and focuses on Southeast Asian Cuisine with Benjamin Cooper at the helm as executive chef.

fields.name: The Edge Of Sahara
fields.information: From the edge of the Sahara to the edge of Perth. Our aim is to bring the amazing tastes of the regions surrounding the largest desert in the world to this growing city. This cuisine has been eaten in these areas for centuries and “The Edge of Sahara” provides an opportunity for you to enjoy these flavours in our city of Perth, on the fringe of its own desert..

fields.name: Jamie's Italian
fields.address: 140 William, 140 William Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: They have a huge team of greeters and seaters, order takers and food deliverers. They were all very efficient and always polite.

fields.name: Mama Tran
fields.address: Shop 10, 36-40 Milligan Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Khuu Thi Gioi is also affectionately known as Mrs Tran by many of her customers. These customers have been frequenting the little corner shop in Palmerston Street, Perth, since the early 80s, being one of the very first Asian gourmet shops of its kind to open in Perth.

fields.name: Shakahari Vegetarian
fields.information:
The name Shakahari, incidentally, is the Hindi word for vegetarian. For more than forty years Shakahari has been one of this city's most innovative restaurants.

Eschewing compromise, Shakahari has maintained a firm commitment to the two fundamentals of its cuisine: It is completely vegetarian and it uses only fresh, natural ingredients. Menus are changed quarterly to take full advantage of seasonally available fruits and vegetables and there are no artificial ingredients or colourants used.

Shakahari has pioneered other fields in its fascinating development. Beginning in the early '70s by introducing ideas from Japanese, Chinese and Thai culinary traditions. In style, Shakahari's cuisine has always been East-West even before this term became the familiar way to describe cooking which uses Asian ingredients and skills in a European context.

Today this restaurant's wide appeal rests on its expertise in creating meals which are light but satisfying, natural but attentively detailed in their preparation and presentation.

In keeping with its original Indian inspiration, the interior design of Shakahari's Carlton location uses basic village tones and simple furnishings. It's only indulgence are two magnificent cloth paintings of the 19th century Nathvara (Rajasthan school) and a series of the earliest devotional posters from the Ravi Varma Steam Press, Poona.

Pure vegetarian menu includes vegan, non-diary and gluten-free dishes. Fresh produce draws fruit, vegetables and herbs from Shakahari's farm in central Victoria.

Reviews from Zomato:

Tasty vegetarian food that makes it feel as though you never need meat in a dish. Satay skewers were probably a stand out followed by their curry. Very well flavored and generous portion sizes!

Avocado magic entree was very good if a little small, and the main courses were delicious. We ordered the satay shakahari and the lasagna, both were amazing.

fields.name: Etro Cafe
fields.address: 49 King Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Etro Bistro lies in the heart of fashion King Street in Perth’s CBD. Offering great coffee and a seasonal a la carte menu for breakfast and lunch. City workers can get a quick bite with great service or grab a baguette to go.

fields.name: Red Man Cucina
fields.address: 116b Walter Road West, Bedford, Morley, Perth
fields.information:
Red Man is not your average Lunch Bar! Good food, good coffee, good vibe. 
Walk-Ins Welcome, Good For Kids, Take Out, Catering and Outdoor Seating

fields.name: Secondeli Cafe
fields.information: Open from 6am to 4pm everyday, providing you all of your caffeine, breakfasts and lunches.

fields.name: Fraser's Restaurant
fields.address: Fraser Avenue, Kings Park, West Perth, Perth, WA
fields.information: Known for its dedication to providing only the best food, wine and service, Fraser’s is the perfect place to celebrate, dine and create lasting memories.

fields.name: The Queens Tavern
fields.information: The Queens Tavern, located in Highgate, is one of Perth’s premier hospitality venues. Originally built in 1889, The Queens underwent extensive renovations in 1986. Today The Queens is a popular contemporary pub with timeless style, where food, friendly staff and great beer come together as one.

fields.name: Thailicious
fields.information:
Reviews from Zomato:

Went here on a Monday night the ding of the microwave, meant it was not a big surprise when steamed rice came out crunchy on to.
Pad thai noodles were gluggy and flavorless.
Massaman curry was tender but very thin. Dont get me started on the satay

Nice Thai restaurant, dint hav a chance to take a picture but next time, will not miss it!
The soup tom zab, goong ob woonsen, simply thai papaya salad are really yum.
The lady who i guess is the manager is really kind and nice to every customer, she often check if our is tasty or if I'd like to add any more favour. 
Luv this one, will surely go back again.

Best thai restaurant ever after considering Ratee Thai and Ying Thai as well. The only reason I love this restaurant most is its food. Eating food in here stimulates my gut to move faster and can even take in more food without feeling any disgust or full. Proper, sufficient taste, just nice! Can't describe how good it was until you try it yourself. Note the varying opening hours before paying a visit to there!

Lovely authentic Thai cuisine with excellent service. Have been there many a time and have even made special trips into the city from the South-Eastern suburbs to eat here. Would recommend to family and friends. Very helpful staff that cater to dietary needs/requests.

fields.information: Davvero! Caffé e Cucina is real food, its kitchen proudly mixing Italian tradition with house made products and carefully selected local produce (didn’t we say we love Western Australia?).

fields.name: Portello Rosso
fields.information:
Concealed behind a red doorway in a covert laneway off Little Bourke street resides Portello Rosso, a small tapas and Jamón restaurant. We pride ourselves on our honest and passionate interpretation of the Spanish way of dining and drinking: shared plates, fresh produce, wines from Spain, Australia and around the world, Sherry, Sidra, Raciones and succulent slices of Jamón, all tied together with relaxed yet professional service.

We cater to both small and large parties, are open for both lunch and dinner, and gladly accept bookings.

The Spanish way of eating is more than just satisfying an empty stomach - food is savoured and indulged communally.
It's not hard to fall in love with their way of life and their cuisine: simple, unpretentious and using only fresh, seasonal and mouth-watering ingredients.

At Portello Rosso, we want to share our experiences and memories with you.

Sit back, relax with a glass of wine, share a bit of everything and we hope you enjoy a little dose of Spain... without the jet-lag.

Reviews from Zomato:

We were seated on the upper floor, which is a narrow dining space best for groups of 2-4. (I found the tables  too close to one another.) The ground floor is a lot more spacious and has larger dining tables. We had a range of small and medium tapas. The standout was the mussels with garlic chilli and tomato. The dish was generous, the mussels were incredibly fresh and meaty, and the whole dish was so delicious. I also really like the croquetas, which were so flavoursome. The crispy pork belly didn't have the puffing crispiness I like, as the skin seemed to be battered and fried. It would have still been okay if the skin and puree underneath weren't both so overwhelmingly salty. On the whole, it was a nice meal with good food.

fields.name: Hey Griller
fields.address: 439 Albany Highway, Victoria Park, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Blending modern Australian cuisine with unmistakable Asian flavours, the menu at Hey Griller is as memorable as the name. The restaurant is perfectly located – sitting just on Albany Highway, the main road that crosses the Swan River – and is decorated with sophistication in mind: ambient lighting, rustic wood and bare brick walls. It gets busy, so reserve a table now
The food at this Victoria Park restaurant is varied and diverse just like Australia itself, and you’ll find everything from succulent steaks to classic Asian cuisine on this extensive menu. There are great cocktails too – we recommend the Glamour Martini when you’re feeling especially fabulous.
The menu at Hey Griller has all the modern Australian delights you could hope for. We can never turn down starters and here, diners can get stuck into a crispy pork belly mini wrap with red bean sauce, crackling and fresh mango, or seared scallops with a gochujang chilli jam. After, become addicted to some fusion skewers: peri peri lamb, tiger prawns – customise as you like. Throw in a whole host of high-quality meats straight from the Asian grill and it’s no wonder regulars return again and again to this Victoria Park steakhouse. Book ahead of time to save your table

fields.name: Slices Family Restaurant

Now that we had the concept in 1999 we thought expansion, this is when we discovered our Keilor location. We figured we could sell pizza's by the slice through drive through, this idea failed miserably! But we did learn alot. Slices diversifed to a family restaurant, we can say kid's love our pizza and our playground. Slices Keilor formed our new concept as times were changing.

Excitingly we have expanded into Caroline Springs and plan to expand all over Melbourne. Caroline Springs targets a new market for us, with amazing views of the Lake a broader range of fantastic customers we are focused on advancing the business.

We are now investing more in our staff, customer feedback and our menu to provide you with a great customer experience. We know you will enjoy our new look Slices venues.

fields.name: Roxby Thai Bar & Grill
fields.address: 398 South Street, O'Connor, Fremantle, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Roxby Thai Bar & Grill is a popular go-to for those who can’t quite decide what they’re in the mood for before they arrive. Sure, on one hand this is one of Perth’s best value Thai eateries, with a full range of traditional classics and modern creations done well, from fish cakes and golden money bags to tom yum, papaya salad, a sizzling satay plate and an amazing ‘fish on fire’ chef’s special featuring fresh barramundi, granny smith apples and cashew nuts in a unique concoction.

This South Street special is also a killer burger joint, with several irresistible optiosn you’ll struggle to match anywhere in Perth like their truffle crumbed chicken or blue cheese steak. We’re not even going to start on Roxby’s famous towering sundaes, either, because we’ll start drooling before we can even finish saying flavours like lychee layers, Black Forest mud cake with mixed berries, crushed Tim Tams with dinner mint pieces...


Roxby Thai Bar & Grill is the place to meet, satisfy your taste buds and enjoy the very relaxing atmosphere at a very reasonable price. We offer the very best in Thai cuisine with a little touch of Western. Only the finest ingredients are used in order to achieve our carefully selected menu. Come and let us spice up your day with one of our great dishes and our wonderful services.

fields.information: The seating is amongst the community garden, and the tables and seating are set on sandy woodchip ground. Serving raw whole foods and salad. Restaurnat photo credit: Brent Derek.

fields.name: The Meatball Bar - Mount Lawley
fields.address: 607 Beaufort Street, Mount Lawley, Perth, WA
fields.information:
As you might imagine, their speciality is meatballs, and the myriad ways that they can be prepared will astound you. Along with the classic Italian meatballs – beef and pork, slow cooked in a Napoli sauce for 12 hours and topped with parmesan, basil and pesto – one can pick up Wagyu beef with Calabrese sausage, bacon-wrapped chicken with cheddar and sweetcorn or wild mushroom and pecorino arancini. 
That is only the tip of the iceberg as far as the meatball options go. The Meatball Bar is an Italian restaurant with an international edge, offering classic dishes from around the world in meatball form. There are harissa lamb meatballs with roasted almonds, raisins and yoghurt, Southern-style buttermilk chicken meatballs with a jalapeno slaw and peanut sauce satay meatballs made from a chicken pork mix, served Malaysian style with pineapple, coriander and rice.

The Meatball Bar has an extensive range of alcoholic beverages from craft beers, exquisite wines and a variety of spirits. We are always introducing new and exciting brands to keep our drinks menu fresh!
Our menu is truly unique—each dish is served as a ball to ensure that every guest enjoys a mouthful of exceptional flavours. It’s a combination of flavours and tastes from around the world.

fields.name: Galangal
fields.address: 180 Scarborough Beach Road, Mount Hawthorn, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Modern authentic Thai and Western influences harmoniously combined into something uniquely "Galangal Cuisine"

Besides being named, short and sweet, after the gingery Southeast Asian plant that’s an essential ingredient in the classic Thai tom yum goong and tom kha kai soups, Galangal is an award-winning legend in Perth’s restaurant landscape. The magic lies in Galangal’s ability to remain down to earth, offering a menu packed with traditional Thai dishes, while elevating the art of Thai cuisine to glamorous heights. The venue, up on the Mount Hawthorn stretch of Scarborough Beach Road, speaks volumes about the quality that the kitchen offers, too, with a dining room decked out in peerless style – white, starched tablecloths against rich, dark, wood-panelled walls. For a taste of Galangal’s upscale Thai dining experience, a reservation is essential.
These days, Galangal is more than a rising star among Perth restaurants, Southeast Asian or otherwise. Having taken out the national award for Best Thai Restaurant in the 2014 Savour Awards For Excellence competition, the reputation of this Mount Hawthorn Thai restaurant is secure. The food here is sensational and, originating from the so-called Land of Smiles, you can expect the service to match, each and every time. Open for dinner from 6pm to 10pm, Tuesday to Sunday, the restaurant’s excellence and relatively limited opening hours have made these tables up on Scarborough Beach Road some of the most sought after in the city.
The food. The delicious nouveau Thai cuisine that this restaurant serves up with endearing, understated artfulness.

Went there around lunchtime last on Friday, the place was packed and took a while to get a seat, loved my coffee, tea and my friend loved her cold brew. 
As I don't eat breads it was a bit hard to pick the right food, and the description of the menu was not very clear how the food actually comes. Eggs Benedict is a sandwich kinda thing. 
Overall the food was nice and the taste was good. I had to deconstruct it but was fine, I just don't like to waste food, understand that it's hard for the kitchen to change things but wasting food is something I really don't like, waiter should take a minute to explain a bit better the food to make it easier to pick something different.

saw a note in the Virgin airlines book to try this place and we weren't disappointed. It is in a not so good part of Melbourne but was absolutely packed and had to wait 30 minutes

However it is very creative and worth going a little noisy and the service needs some work .

Really nice place to catch up with friends. The size of pancake fitted 2 persons to eat! Can't eat alone! Really full! It's good to share for the afternoon tea with friends. Will still go next time.

Great service, great coffee, great venue. Food is simple and good. However, this is my fav spot in CBD for breaky or brunch because the design is amazing and its spacious, so we can breath while enjoying food and great coffee here.

fields.name: Monk Bodhi Dharma
fields.address: Rear of 202 Carlisle Street, St Kilda East, Melbourne
fields.information:
Now open Friday nights for dinner, two sittings 6.30pm and 8.30pm. To book, please phone 03 9534 7250 or email info@monkbd.com.au

Delicious raw vegan living food menu items to discover including the signature raw vegan ice cream.

Now taking wholesale coffee accounts... and beans available for home!

Reviews from Zomato:

Tucked away in an alley behind the main road, Monk Bodhi Dharma feels secret and cosy. The interior is much smaller than I expected but warm and comfortable. Came on a weekday lunchtime and was able to choose a table. Service was nice and friendly, they didn't rush us at all even though my friend was late to arrive. We shared the umami mushrooms and the Acai bowl. The mushrooms were delicious, flavoursome and tender. The acai bowl was fresh and yummy. A little on the sweet side, but it was my first acai bowl so I can't compare. The soy chai has a delicious spicy kick to it, but at $7 for a mug (that being said, it comes in an awesome mug) it's rather steep -- probably wouldn't order again. Keen to come back and try the tacos and apple pancakes.

Tiny place hidden down the laneway between Woolworths and the shops. Managed to get a seat on the communal table which was a bit squishy and hard to get out of without disturbing everyone's breakfast. Staff were friendly but slow, the laid back vibe has been taken too far unfortunately. Ordered a $7 chai latte (ridiculously priced) that turned up burning hot and half way through my meal. The people sitting next to us never got a menu or their drinks. The food menu is impressive with lots of options. Settled for the buckwheat pancakes and partner got the bean tacos. Food was sensational and had high quality ingredients! Overall great vegetarian/vegan food, but overpriced drinks and inattentive staff are it's downfalls!

fields.name: Manchester Press
fields.information:
Reviews from Zomato:

 Lovely fresh bagels! We had the pulled pork and the recommended smoked salmon. Both were good, though I secretly wished I'd ordered the smoked salmon one instead! Interesting to experience my brunch served with pretzels. Coffee was so so, would return to try the sweet bagel options!

Coffee is nice sometime but depending on who made the coffee, there are several time that I went there, the coffee tasted watery, there is no consistency. Bagel is very nice (I used to like the banana and bacon).

Place is cute but the food is real average, had a bagel was nice but a bit dry. 
Drinks are very good though !! 
Service was good as well. 

We have a pulls pork today. The pork wasn't very taste by itself, so we put extra spice and sauce to up the flavor. we are little bit disappointed. The cafe is average. The service is quite good

""This cafe is tucked away in the CBD but make sure you get there early or else you might have to wait in line!! Manchester Press is bagel heaven with loads of options! I chose the vegan option which included vegan cream cheese, pumpkin and spinach. 
Honestly I didn't really like the cream cheese - but I don't like the dairy version either! The avocado smash option was so delicious and the coffee is perfect too! 
Such a nice little spot in the city 💕""

Fantastic coffee, I also ordered the bagel with avocado which was tasty, it came with a side of pretzel. Nice ambience had an industrial feel about it.

fields.name: Post
fields.address: Ground Floor, COMO The Treasury, State Buildings, 1 Cathedral Avenue, Perth
fields.information: World-class cuisine is a core experience at all COMO Hotels and Resorts, recognised by numerous industry awards, including Michelin stars.

fields.name: Cafe One58
fields.information:
"Café One58 is in the top 3 restaurants in mandurah and offers comfortable clean indoor and Alfresco Style dinning.

Pete and Jenni have a great Café with great service and food options to suit all customers with vegetarian choices also available. Bookings are suggested."

fields.name: Miss Chow's

Whether it's breakfast or lunch, head chef Justin Peters is constantly striving to produce food that is diverse, thoughtful & delicious. They are truly dedicated to our local customers.

fields.name: Secret Kitchen
fields.information:
Our Chinese Cuisine Executive Chef and Dim Sim Executive Chef have both enjoyed an extensive career in hospitality spanning between 20-35 years.

They have both created many innovative dishes that won multiple nationally recognized awards in China.

Working closely with their culinary team, Our chefs infuse the principles of fine Chinese cuisine, aroma, flavour and presentation in every dish.

Reviews from Zomato:

Standard Yum Cha fare available here, it seems that there isn't a particular signature dish! ... a nice atmosphere and reasonable service... tables are at least spaced appropriately unlike other city yum Cha... and the food is tasty..

Great place for yumcha and/or dinner!! Dinner isn't cheap though especially peking duck - prep for us so does look a but sad. $39 for half (8pc) and $59 for full (16pc). Its ok, the pork belly fried rice was delicious though! Very tasty with plenty of pork belly. Service is efficient.

Definitely one of the top notch place for Yum Cha. Large, modern and spacious settings, with lots of variety of dishes to choose from. Much better than shark fin inn, and other yum cha places in the CBD. Generous portion and fresh ingredients. Added to my fave list for yum cha.

We booked a 12.20pm seating for Yum Cha on Sunday, didn't get seated until 12.30.  There were very few trolleys coming to the area our table was at, so not much selection.  My partner had to ask the waiter a few times if they could wheel more dim sum trolleys our way but to no avail.  The dim sum is of very good quality but service is lacking behind by a long way, that's why the 2.5 rating.

fields.name: Canvas Cafe
fields.information: Grab a coffee in the secret courtyard, or you can sit in the sun on the Art Center's front lawn. Plenty of parking available and in the centre of Fremantle.

fields.information: Great cafe for a catch up with friends - parking is relatively easy on a weekday, lovely decor of a fully functioning bookshop setting and cheerful workers. Fine for a low key delicious baked goodie or light lunch.

fields.name: Dip In Cafe

fields.name: Dainty Dowager

fields.name: Desi Dhaba

Authentic, tasty and flavored with true spices to come up with original and unique dishes that come from the street eateries of Indian Highways.

fields.name: Prime House
fields.address: The Court, 500 Bourke Street, CBD, Melbourne
fields.information:
Prime House is the ultimate home for true lovers of exquisitely delicious roast & grilled meat, home-made burgers, tasty hot sandwiches & fine coffee.

If you love flame-grilled and barbecued meat then we are glad to meet you! Choose from our homemade burgers, pork belly open sandwich, lamb kebabs and grilled chicken salad.

All our prime patties are homemade and are available in lamb, beef, chicken. With the chef’s signature burgers comprising unique ingredients and combinations, your palate will love you!

Also available is a great selection of local and international beers & wines as well as our award-winning coffee.

Reviews from Zomato:

Went there to use groupon voucher and even though it was difficult to find, it is actually pretty nice with courtyard and area you can sit outside. We had the pork crackling bun and moroccan lamb burger. I was disappointed with the pork bun because when you hear crackling, of course you think it will be sooo gooood. However I find the pulled pork needs more flavour. It is very tender, but the amount of crackle is really small and I dont find them fresh. The moroccan lamb burger has more taste. The chips are good.

Come often for a open steak sandwich or 150g Porterhouse steak, both $19!!!Both are very good and reasonable price for lunch time option.
Very tasty

Coming in hot with the Prime House 16 hour Roast Pulled Pork & Crackling Burger. 
Deliciously handcrafted bun bursting with succulent pork and crackling, did not skimp on the amount of pork, the coleslaw complementing the pork could have been slightly fresher, however nice variation from the traditional burger. The fries we found to be a fair bit stale.

fields.name: Raffles Hotel Perth
fields.address: 70-72 Canning Beach Road, Applecross, Melville, Perth, WA
fields.information: The Raffles Hotel has been the ‘people’s local’ of Perth for nearly 120 years – from the ‘refreshments at the dancehall’ days of the 1800’s, the swinging social scene of the 40’s and 50’s and her rock’n’roll phase of the 70’s & 80’s.

fields.name: Longrain Melbourne
fields.information:
Welcome to Longrain, Melbourne, continuing to evolve Martin Boetz's original Longrain vision with a menu that brings together South East Asian influences with the best Victorian produce. Inspired by the communal eating philosophy of the Asian table, our menu is made up of dishes created for sharing. Large servings and communal tables encourage the spirit of eating together, so you can try each dish as part of a full tasting experience, just as it was intended. The wine and cocktail list is created to work in harmony with the menu's intense and aromatic flavours.

Longrain Melbourne is a contemporary restaurant and bar uniquely located within an expansive, 100-year-old converted warehouse-style building. The hip yet welcoming atmosphere, combined with warm and friendly service, original cocktails and an inspired wine list can also be found at Longrain Melbourne. 

COCKTAIL BAR

Dividing the cocktail lounge from the main dining area, the bar is the heart of the Longrain space. This is where our talented bartenders create beautiful twists on the classics, taking inspiration from the bright, zesty flavours of South East Asia. Come early and wait for your table with a stick drink while you watch the chefs shred chillies through the kitchen window. Perfect for pre and post-theatre drinks, the bar is open from early evening till late.

Reviews from Zomato:

The betel leaf with poach prawn, caramelised pork hock and yellowfin tuna tartare are my highlights! The venue light is very dimmed and intimate. Service was great. One of my fav thai fusion restaurant in Melbourne besides Chin chin.

Expensive for what it is. Had the banquet and all the dishes were too sweet. Stunning dessert of the day though. Eggnet is definitely worth ordering for the novelty value.

fields.name: Odyssea Beach Cafe
fields.information: With spectacular views of the ocean and beach, Odyssea brings a new dining experience to Western Australia’s iconic coastline. Their modern-Australian menu offers sophisticated beach side fare with a focus on local producers and seasonality. Whenever possible we try to make everything in-house, including specialty cakes and desserts.

fields.information: Arthouse - A fresh and bright ‘modern Australian bistro’ (fancier than a café but more relaxed than a restaurant) at the Art Gallery of WA.

fields.information: They offer a wonderful selection of Vegetarian, Vegan, Raw & Gluten-free Food and pride themselves on catering to all their customer's dietary requirements.

fields.name: Don Tapa

fields.information: Modern South American & Asian Fusion Cuisine with bold flavours, casual vibe, excellent customer service and dangerously delicious cocktails.

fields.name: Din Tai Fung
fields.address: Emporium Melbourne, Level 4, 287 Lonsdale Street, CBD, Melbourne
fields.information:
Once described by world renowned chef Ken Hom as the world's tastiest dumpling, it may seem strange that there is such an art to eating something no bigger than the average mouthful.

Din Tai Fung has a signature point of difference - every pork dumpling pastry is delicately hand made to measure between precisely 4.8 and 5.2 grams at conception, before being filled to weigh between 20.8 and 21.2 grams. All this and the promise that the pork dumplings are made fresh in front of your eyes, steamed in exactly three minutes and on your table in seconds. Such scientific precision and quality control is what makes Din Tai Fung stand out from the rest.

The first Din Tai Fung that opened in 1972 was only a humble stall in Taipei. Din Tai Fung restaurants can now be found in Taiwan, Australia, Japan, USA, Singapore, China, Indonesia, Korea, Malaysia, Hong Kong, Macau and Thailand.

Reviews from Zomato:

Good, but not great. Prompt service, feels a little forced, but attentive. Don't get me wrong, the dumplings here are delicious, but our party of 4 all thought they lacked flavour, in terms of salt & 'seasoning'. Crab steamed dumplings were definitely the stand out. Honestly, wouldn't go back.""

Delicious and always great service at Din Tai Fung! Vegetarians have plenty of options if you look at the menu closely. I recommend the spicy wontons with noodles, garlic with spinach and the vegetables truffle fried rice for something different. The Thai milk iced tea smoothie is a must to help put out the fire of the spicy wontons.

fields.name: Clarences Bar & Eats

fields.name: Chu Bakery

fields.name: Henry Saw
fields.information: Vegan & plant based friendly including wraps, pies, sweet treats, smoothies, tea and even Kombucha.

fields.name: Left Bank Bar and Cafe
fields.address: 15 Riverside Road, East Fremantle, Fremantle, Perth, WA
fields.information: Located on the banks of the beautiful Swan River, the Left Bank is the perfect spot for some relaxing drink and fantastic food while enjoying in the amazing view.

fields.name: Pondok Rempah
fields.information:
Pondok Rempah, or translated “House of Spices”, is an Indonesian restaurant based in Melbourne, Australia. Located at the heart of city centre Melbourne, just one step away from Victoria Market. Our restaurant offers a unique authentic Indonesian cuisine experience that was derived from the passions brought by our chefs from all over Indonesia, who combined and created Indonesian-fusion food alive in our restaurant very soon!

Since 2016, we’ve provided guests with a fine balance of casual yet elegant Indonesian food that suit both Asian and Australian palates. Filled with a modern yet original Indonesian flavours, our missions are to give the most authentic Indonesian flavors and to promote Indonesian culinary to our guests.

To make sure our goal as the best Indonesian Restaurant in Melbourne is achieved, regular guests and first time diners will always be welcomed here at Pondok Rempah. Experience the friendliness of Indonesian hosts and the strong flavors of Indonesian spices from our wide-ranged skilled chefs.

We are also proud to claim ourselves as the first Indonesian street-food seller in Melbourne.

Enjoy a day for just strolling around Melbourne and buy some light street foods, such as “grilled satay” ordered at our shop’s windows’ panel, or you can do an indoor-lunch and dining and order some of our famous signature dishes such as “Oxtail Soup“ and “Sweet and Sour Fish”. Our innovative menu and strategic location have made us a popular rendezvous for Melbourne’s business community, local residents, visitors and tourists alike.

If you’re planning on joining us soon, why not stop by or book now by click on Contact Us page and experience a vacation to South East Asian in between your hectic days. We look forward to the pleasure of your company very soon!

fields.name: Heirloom
fields.information: Heirloom is a Modern Japanese and Sake Bar showcasing a modern take on some traditional Japanese Izakaya dishes, sharing dishes, and has an exclusive and extensive selection of sake, boutique wines, local and Japanese micro-brewery beers, and Melbourne's largest collection of Japanese whiskies.

fields.name: Third Wave Cafe
fields.information: Third Wave has become a religious experience on the Melbourne restaurant scene. Since opening in 2010, we have cemented a reputation as a great neighbourhood cafe with a loyal breakfast and lunch crowd. Avacordo

fields.name: Fukutontei

fields.name: Good Ovening
fields.information: Korean restaurant.

fields.name: Matisse Beach Club

fields.information:
Lucy Liu is an eclectic multicultural Asian eating & drinking space designed to cater for sharing tastes in a fun street food environment.

Reviews:

I went here for after work drinks and an early meal mid week and overall it was good. It was fairly expensive for what you get and that is why I would only give it a 3.5. Venue is nice and so were the staff.

Was pleasantly surprised, had heard mixed reviews previously. 
Had the soft shell crab pancake bun that was amazing, so was the pork belly. Unfortunately the Sichuan duck was not Sichuan, and more of a mildly sweet sauce. 
Recommend reservations as it was fully booked.

Didn't really live up to the hype.

I was expecting some pretty big this with LL and I was a bit disappointed. The food was good without being excellent. I'd go to Kong bbq before returning here. 

The chicken ribs and dumplings were the standouts from what I had on the menu. The service was good, however it is loud in there (which is probably expected in these types of eateries). 

Good if you like Asian tap beers, as there a couple nice ones on the menu.

Great food but terrible service. Was given an hour to order and eat. Wait staff would constantly come over and harass you to order. Couldn't even order desert because we had gone over our 'time'. It's a shame cause the food is very good. Would recommend one of Melbourne's other top restaurants like chin chin or super normal, which are just around the corner.

fields.name: Layup
fields.information: We're all about great coffee, house baked bread, killer brunch and providing awesome service to an awesome neighbourhood!

fields.name: The Hardware Store Cafe & Eatery

fields.name: Don Don
fields.information:
Reviews from Zomato:

Had a bento box from here... well it is cheap but pretty average... the cucumbers in the salad were not freshly cut and beef question mark was not to my taste. Mediocre but cheap. They are obviously targeting the RMIT student market.

Friendly staff, super fast service and yummy food. Great value for money. We've tried a few things on the menu and everything was delicious. Only a couloir of minutes from melbourne central so great to have a quick meal here before or after movie

Just around the corner from the Melbourne Central fashion strip, Don Don is a great place to take your wife once she's all shopped out. We went for the sashimi and curry chicken dons and were presented within 5 minutes with two massive bowls of rice, veggies, our@ respective meats, and in my case a well-spiced curry. All for only $8 a bowl! And in the hour we were there their impressive noughties jukebox managed to not play a single Taylor Swift song. Their airborne biological waste disposal system was cute though perhaps not so hygienic and some of their ingredients were perhaps a little bland, with little variety to choose from. The only real preclusion to a 5.0 rating was the cash only status. Otherwise, the best value Japanese food I've ever had!

Amazing customer service once again, and it's been a year since I've been to Don Don and my experience is just as great as the first time! Very affordable prices too

fields.name: Bib & Tucker
fields.address: 18 Leighton Beach Boulevard, North Fremantle, Fremantle, Perth, WA
fields.information: Situated above the iconic Fremantle Surf Life Saving Club, the restaurant is always buzzing with friendly activity and conversation.

fields.name: Laksa Bar

fields.name: Catch 22 Tapas & Cocktail Lounge
