fields.name: George Street Quarters
fields.address: 71 - 75 George Street, East Fremantle, Fremantle, Perth, WA
fields.information: Enjoy people watching amongst their heritage surrounds, whilst sitting street side on beautiful George street, or venture inside for an inviting casual dining experience.

fields.name: Voyage Kitchen
fields.address: 128 West Coast Drive, Sorrento, Perth, WA
fields.information: Voyage opened it's doors for the first time in January 2004. Simply cooked,fresh food, good coffee,warm and friendly service, was and remains our mission.

fields.name: The Toff In Town
fields.address: Curtin House, Level 2, 252 Swanston Street, CBD, Melbourne, VIC
fields.information:
The Toff’s main bar or ‘carriage room’ is fitted out with a unique train carriage running down the centre, made up of booths which can be reserved for dining. Each booth can be made as private as desired by closing doors, pulling down blinds and using the discreet buzzer for service-evoking the intimacy and elegance of early 20th century train travel.

The restaurant created by chef Karen Batson boasts a Thai menu, designed to be shared in an intimate Toff booth. There is a sophisticated beverage list to match, with local and imported beers, wines and spirits. Cocktails are available for those who wish to add an extra splash of decadence to their evening.

The mood is set by local DJs playing lush, dark and sexy sounds into the wee hours of the morning-with the bar and kitchen opened until 3am weekdays and 5am on the weekends.

The Toff’s stage room hosts the full spectrum of Australian performing arts including music (from pop to country to ensembles), dance, comedy, and theatre, as well as touring international acts. Described as ‘a naughty room with an intimate cabaret feel’ the space has a capacity ranging from 150 (fully seated) to 300 (standing only). Featuring live music most nights of the week, the room transforms into a nightclub later into the night featuring local DJs weekly plus international guests on a regular basis.

Review from Zomato:

Good place for a drink if you are in a small group not suitable for large groups as there is limited seating. Cocktails are nice and they have a small food offering.

fields.name: Lane's Edge
fields.information: Lane's Edge cafe/bar has proven over the past 14 years to be one of Melbourne's best hidden treasures with its consistently good food, service and drinks at an appealing price.

fields.name: The Hardware Societe
fields.information:
Hidden down one of Melbourne’s many alleyways, Hardware Societe needs no introduction as one of the more popular brunch places in the area.

Reviews from Zomato:

Great awesome food. They cater to preg women. Staff was really good at recommending. A plus for me. 😍 The baked eggs apparently a fav with preg women and done so good. Flavours worked really well. Really enjoyed my hot chocolate too - a great combo melting the choc. My husband mentioned the coffee was really good too and he's got a high standard for coffee so was definitely a plus for him. He also had the lobster with bun, mayo and poached eggs. My friend had scrambled eggs with bun, bacon, and capsicum purée. We cleaned out our plates not because we were hungry but the food was really delicious. It's been awhile since we've been but worth the long queue beforehand. We live a bit of a distance from the city but if we head back that way, definitely visiting again to try the other things on the menu.

Another favorite join for my breakfast or brunch is this place, it has an amazing food and coffee. It has consistently great service and always queue-ING!  I tend to bring interstate or international client in this place to enjoy their stay in Melbourne and experience great food.

The pictures say it all. Definitely one of the best place for brunch/lunch I've ever been. This place is one of my favourite. Love their pork belly and the duck confeit. The coffee is well done as well and i like they are using such a pretty cup. Totally recommended. Good for all kind of occasion. Indoor/outdoor seatings are available but be prepared to queue.

fields.name: The Precinct
fields.address: 834 Albany Highway, Victoria Park, Perth, WA
fields.information: The Precinct is a relaxed, casual and cozy venue situated on the bustling Albany Hwy cafe strip in East Victoria Park. The Precinct takes pride in sourcing ingredients that are fresh and in-season to create dishes that are rustic and homely via a shared concept menu making the produce the feature and the hero of the dish.

fields.name: Pepper Lunch
fields.address: Shop 5, 95 Barrack Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: At Pepper Lunch, you are our master Chef. We assemble the finest & freshest ingredients on our patented sizzling hot teppan and you simply immerse yourself in the culinary and wholesome experience of ‘Sizzling it your Way’. For a different twist, experiment with our exquisitely crafted sauces to create a taste of your own!

fields.name: Chilli Everest
fields.information: Chilli Everest provides Authentic Nepalese food

fields.name: Frisch & Barc
fields.address: 297 Canning Highway, Como, South Perth, Perth, WA
fields.information: In 1886 Vienna, Austria, a baby by the name of Karl Ritter von Frisch was born. In his lifetime, Frisch grew up to become an ethologist (someone who studies animal behaviour), and during his heydey​, Frisch studied the social and communicative interaction of European honeybees.

fields.name: Lot Twenty

fields.name: Gingerboy
fields.information:
ICONIC MELBOURNE RESTAURANT GINGERBOY IS RENOWNED FOR ITS FUNKY DÉCOR, ASIAN-INSPIRED DISHES AND HIP LANEWAY LOCATION. SERVING CREATIVE STREET FOOD, BASED AROUND PLATES FOR SHARING, CHEF TEAGE EZARD TAKES A UNIQUE AND BOLD APPROACH TO FOOD OF THE REGION.
The dining experience at Gingerboy is centred on a modern Australian adaptation of hawker-style street food. The restaurant’s hustle and bustle is a sharp intersection of sophisticated New York dining culture, and the frenzy and buzz of Asian hawker markets.
Menus at Gingerboy are written according to the seasons. The approach over the colder months is to braise, steam and stew, using rich, deep flavours. Cooking in the warmer climate brings more refreshing, crisp, and vibrant flavours to the menu. We use each ingredient at the height of its flavour, colour, appearance and quality. This approach in our philosophy is the most significant, as it delivers consistently great dishes.

Reviews from Zomato:

Incredibly disappointing. Bad first impression from a surly host, progressed to forgotten orders, corked wine, tasteless food and multiple errors that became quite comic at one point. We've been planning to come to this Melbourne institution for ages but can't imagine coming back.

This place is superb.. the food is to die for (especially the duck spring rolls )and the service exceptional. Highly recommended. Good spot for a meal before the theatre.

One of Melbourne's best restaurants that we keep coming back to for its flawless, attentive service and tonight was no exception. The venue was at full capacity but the service and food didn't skip a beat to the point that the waiter noticed too much chilli in our salad and brought a new one within a minute...nice! Thanks so much Gingerboy. Will be back again real soon.

fields.name: The Trustee Bar and Bistro
fields.address: Brookfield Place, 133 St Georges Terrace, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Housed in the majestic WA Trustees building on St Georges Terrace in the CBD, The Trustee satisfies the hungry and wine curious of Perth. With Chef Andre Mahe at the helm, expect humble, full flavoured bistro fare made passion.

fields.name: Samsons Paddock
fields.information: Samson’s Paddock is a bar and restaurant situated in Mosman Park. Work on the most recent incarnation began in 2014, but the site has a history of being a favourite watering hole for local people since Lionel Samson first purchased the land back in 1831.

fields.name: La Veen Coffee & Kitchen
fields.address: 90 King Street, Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Upon entering the heritage-listed building on the corner of King and Wellington streets, the amazing primeval brickwork and near floor-to-ceiling windows are dwarfed by the behemoth of an espresso machine which decorates the front bench. A six group, 2nd generation Synesso Hydra, powder coated black with Bubinga wood handles and ‘toggles’ by Reg Barber, is paired with two black modded Mazzer Roburs and a matching Black Malkonig EKK43.

fields.name: Mapo Grill

fields.information: Funky cool Asian fusion restaurant bar that showcases innovative fusion of food and drinks with Japanese Green tea.

fields.name: Fuyu

fields.information: Takes Reservations, Walk-Ins Welcome, Good For Groups, Catering, Waiter Service and Outdoor Seating.

fields.name: Cookie

fields.information: Popular for being one of Melbourne's best bars, Cookie offers a great selection of cocktails in a dynamic environment. Cookie’s versatility is highlighted by the fact that it also operates as a Thai restaurant with a large space adjacent to the bar reserved for dining patrons.

fields.name: Takumi
fields.information:
Japanese owned and operated Takumi is a new concept Japanese restaurant specializing in only the highest quality Wagyu with the largest selections of Wagyu prime cuts currently available in Australia. Let your senses take you on a cooking journey as you explore the various cuts of Wagyu, after all its destiny is in your hands.

Offering a selections of unique signature dishes including Takumi’s style Wagyu tenderloin carpaccio, salmon sashimi infused with carrot and onion sauce and Japanese soba salad, Takumi is one of Melbourne’s favourite destination for fine Japanese dining. Enhance your experience with a wide range of authentic sake, shochu and fine national wines for selection. 

The restaurant is spacious, comfortable and relaxing. At Takumi, we pride ourselves on our ability to provide a warm and friendly service to enhance your dining experience. 

If you are after a unique dinning experience, Takumi is fast getting a reputation as a restaurant you can’t just go past.

Reviews from Zomato:

Value for money 10 course Japanese degustation Groupon voucher $99 for 2, generous and quality dishes w Sake. There are two sessions 6pm or 8pm and we found it little rush to finish each course. Overall we enjoyed our dinner tonight. Friendly service by Japanese waitresses too.

Pleasantly surprised with this lunch spot - reasonable prices for good Japanese food. Salmon special recommend (comes with traditional miso). The staff are very helpful with special dietary requirements.

I really enjoyed my dinner here tonight. The meat was really tender and flavoursome however I've had better. The menu is very limited! The entrees were nice, I really enjoyed that takumi special and the chicken balls! For dessert I recommend getting the red bean ice cream so freaking good!

fields.name: The Apple Daily Bar & Eating House

It has been quite the journey and we are sure it’s just the beginning . We have got our hearts set on making more history.

fields.name: Tazio Birraria Pizzeria Cucina
fields.information:
Situated on the corner of Exhibition Street and Flinders Lane, Tazio is in the company of the best Flinders Lane restaurants in Melbourne CBD.

Having opened in 2005, Tazio was the first traditional Italian pizza restaurant in Melbourne CBD’s Paris end.

The restaurant specializes in offering traditional Italian style pizza and contemporary Italian-Australian cuisine in a casual dining setting.

Complimenting the cuisine are two bars with an extensive selection of local and imported beers, wines, cocktails and spirits.

With 10 sections and 240 seats both indoor and outdoor area spanning across two floors, Tazio is the largest Italian restaurant in Melbourne CBD.

The venue is set in a multi level layout which accommodates everything from romantic dinners and birthdays to large engagement parties and corporate functions.

On the web, Tazio is regularly rated among the best Italian restaurants in Melbourne on Zomato, Google and TripAdvisor.

Reviews from Zomato:

One of my favourite places in Melbourne. Food is always good but the service is the best I've ever encountered. The owner Ray goes above and beyond to make sure everyone leaves with a smile.

We had our Christmas function here - wonderful service and delicious food! the staff were so friendly and accommodating, and everything went perfectly. Everyone that came loved it, the food was plentiful and the balcony was the perfect spot for it.

We held a function with Tazio and it was great! They made it feel so special and unique, everything was easy and gave great service in the lead up to the event and on the night. Everything from naming a signature cocktail for us, so customized menus for those with dietary requirements. We all left feeling full and had a great time.

fields.name: Punch Lane
fields.information:
Owner Martin Pirc has amassed an eclectic bunch of curios artifacts, collating the unique findings together in a refurbished police station. Salvaged from an old basketball court in Healesville, the rich timber bar made up of 100 year-old-jarrah floorboards, hand-crafted wrought iron fixtures, & red leather chairs worn by The Beatles on their 1964 tour to Australia are just some of the priceless furnishings that make Punch Lane the beautiful venue you see today. Designed by acclaimed Melbourne architects Jackson, Clements, & Burrows, the dining area on Little Bourke St provides the perfect spot to sit & watch the world go by. This slightly eccentric, yet clever design has also won Punch Lane the 2005 Urban Architecture Award.
With so much to offer, Punch Lane is set to impress anyone who is looking for a true Melbourne laneway gem.

Reviews from Zomato:

The scallops were some of the best I've had and my partners wallaby was incredible. Some of the most unique and interesting flavour combinations we have experienced in Melbourne. The bar menu (and staff) were also great - so will certainly be back for a wine and cheese night!

We celebrated an amazing evening at this fantastic restaurant. As a party of seven we were looked after like royalty. Our food was incredible, atmosphere superb and service impeccable. Congratulations Punch Lane!

awesome food service and ambience ... we had our office Xmas dinner and enjoyed the food and hospitality of the friendly staff ... will definitely return

fields.name: Hakata Gensuke Ramen Professionals
fields.information:
Hakata Gensuke is a Japanese noodle bar located on 168 Russell Street in Melbourne CBD. Gensuke is specialized in pork bone noodle soup and dipping noodle also known as Tonkotsu Ramen and Tsukemen. Our Inventor and shop owners Master Chef Kousuke Yoshimura has brought the real taste of Hakata tonkotsu ramen to Australia for the first time.

The ever important soup
Gensuke tonkotsu is prepared using “Yobimodoshi” (master stock) method to ensure a flavorful soup virtually only found in Japan’s best ramen dining experiences. With 7 top of the range stock cookers they will be churning out hundreds a liters a day to serve all of our hungry guests. Also using only the highest quality fresh pork bones from reputable Australian suppliers our team of chefs will not only inspect but also eat a full bowl daily ensuring its highest quality before serving to our guests. 

Noodles
Gensuke noodle is made in house in a temperature, climate and humidity control room with the same best equipment used is every single ramen shop in the Hakata Gensuke group. The specialized Gensuke blend of flour with be scrutinized every step of the way by Master Chef Kousuke and his team. The noodle is considered slightly more chewy and flatter than typical Hakata noodles and patrons will have the option to choose the firmness of their noodles and order extra servings if they require.

fields.name: Hawker's Cuisine
fields.information: A Malaysian hawker food establishment in Perth. Popular dishes include Marmite chicken, Fuzhou tofu or the butter prawns.

fields.name: Oree Korean Duck Restaurant
fields.information:
Oree' means duck in Korean. (오리)
 
We are the very first Korean style duck BBQ restaurant in Australia.
 
Korean traditionally eat duck as health food.
 
Duck is high in unsaturated fat, a healthier fat known to lower blood triglycerides and increase good cholesterol.
Our duck dish has a savory taste that different from other meat.
 
Oree' is the only place where you can enjoy fresh meat BBQ in Melbourne. We use fresh duck meat, locally produced and deboned by our chef. 9grade-Wagyu beef and organic farmed black pork are also on the menu.
 
We serve not only BBQ, but also many different traditional korean dishes like Bibimbab, Bulgogi, Army stew, Korean sushi, Tteokbokki etc. as well known all over the world.
 
Now, we would like to introduce why duck meat is healthy!
 
< Food Value of Duck >
 
Duck meat makes a healthful addition to your diet, offers several nutrients important for tissue function and helps you boost your protein intake.
 
Duck fat is high in Unsaturated fat which have amazing health benefits, including :
 
-Reduced cholesterol levels. The American Heart Association recommends the consumption of MUFAs to improve your blood lipid profile.
 
-Lower risk for heart disease and stroke. Diets with monounsaturated fats correlate with healthy hearts and fewer strokes.
 
-Weight loss. Studies have found that switching to monounsaturated fat from diets with trans fats and polyunsaturated fats results in weight loss.
 
-Less severe pain and stiffness for sufferers of rheumatoid arthritis. Diet plays a role in improving the pain and stiffness of those who already have rheumatoid arthritis.

fields.name: Hibachi Japanese Grill
fields.information: Situated in busy King Street, Hibachi Japanese Grill is a relaxing haven away from the hustle and bustle, with 4 cosy and elegant Tatami rooms perfect for functions or business meetings.

fields.name: Shandong Mama
fields.address: Midcity Arcade, Shop 7, 200 Bourke Street, CBD, Melbourne
fields.information:
Our in-house made dumpling skins come in three different grades of thickness to match the filling and method of cooking. While the fish dumplings taste best in a thin, translucent skin, which allows prompt cooking, the meat dumplings need thicker skin to withstand longer cooking.Our food made freshly from quality ingredients hand picked and prepared by Mama herself. 

Mama is very passionate about gourmet food, and while she enjoys following the traditional fare, she also loves to create new recipes inspired by Melbourne’s diverse food culture and ingredients. For Mama dumplings are an art form, not just a passion, it’s an obsession!

Reviews from Zomato:

Really bland. The noodles in gravy were bland & slimey, served in a big bowl to share. How to eat that without a plate? Who knows. Dumplings were okay but not exciting & not particularly fresh. Terribly overpriced & disappointing

Very popular restaurant but we did not have to wait for long time to get a table as we came already pas the busy lunch hour. I was curious to try the rice dishes from this restaurant so I ordered Egg and Chives Stir-fry on Rice. I didn't have to wait long to get the order. When it came, it was quite a generous portion and I enjoyed it.

Came here after hearing a lot about their dumplings, but was a little bit disappointed. We ordered 2 boiled dumplings, 2 fried dumplings, a noodle dish, an eggplant dish and a fishball soup. The soup tasted a little strange and unpleasant, but the eggplant was super crispy and delicious! The dumplings, however, were not the best. The wrappers kept on breaking or sticking onto the plate! Also, we wanted to order a fish dish, but they said we'd have to wait a whole hour before we could get it! Very disappointing.

fields.name: Lalla Rookh Bar & Eating House
fields.address: Lalla Rookh Bar & Eating House Allendale Square, 77 St Georges Terrace (Lower Ground), Perth CBD, Perth, WA
fields.information: Grab a drink and a bite to eat in the courtyard, bar or lounge. Gather in the dining room for an il Capo feast or if you're after a special drop to drink in or takeaway head to the Wine Store.

fields.name: Simply Spanish
fields.information:
Simply Spanish is all about celebrating the best of food and drink in a fun and lively atmosphere. We believe in using the season’s best produce, going local where possible and creating food which is fresh, exciting and delicious. Everyday, you can watch as paellas are being prepared in our giant pans or even sneak a peak into our open kitchen as the chefs dish up some of the most delightful, heart warming tapas with influences from all parts of Spain.

Our team is like a family and our restaurant is like our home. So, as families do, we welcome you into our home to bring you a little taste of Spain through our food, drink and experience. We have ample seating outdoors and a cozy, colourful interior for you to either enjoy a quick coffee fix, hearty breakfast or a little snack to beat that afternoon slump. Better yet, kick back and relax with friends or family and graze away on tapas, paellas and a sangria or two (or five!).

 

Harry Mangat, Head Chef

Harry has been with Simply Spanish from day one. His passion and interest for food stems from his childhood, watching his mother and aunts prepare the family’s everyday meal. After heading the kitchen at South Melbourne for 3 years, Harry spent time improving his knowledge and skills at other top Melbourne restaurants including; Lamaro’s, The Smith, Hare & Grace and a ‘stage’ at Attica in Ripponlea. Now returning to head the team at Simply Spanish QVM, he’s excited to be back with a team he regards as family.

fields.name: Coda
fields.information:
Located in one of Melbourne’s most iconic laneways Coda exists in the heart of the city’s most dynamic culinary precinct. A stone’s throw away from the Yarra River, Flinders Street station and Federation Square, Coda opens its doors for lunch and dinner seven days a week. From frequenting locals who live and work nearby to guests from across the globe Coda hosts a diverse group of diners welcome for any occasion.

Entering the restaurant you will be greeted by a member of our dedicated team headed by Mykal and Kate Bartholomew and Executive Chef Adam D’Sylva. The trio has assembled a dedicated team with highly sought-after experience from many international and Melbourne restaurants.

Since 2009  we are thrilled to have maintained One Hat in The Age Good Food Guide’s ‘HatAward’ and are also very proud of our Head Sommelier Travis Howe, previously awarded Sommelier of the Year and Wine List of the Year.

Coda’s relaxed environment provides a versatile setting for a range of engagements whatever your occasion. From a quick pre-football meal to a long Sunday lunch, business dining or a cosy seat for an anniversary, we look forward to your visit.

While bookings are highly recommended, patrons without a reservation can enjoy the full menu at the bar.

Reviews from Zomato:

Been years since I've been back here again, and definitely worth the revisit ! Food was spectacular, and so was service. :) don't skip out on all the delicious little nibbles on the entree menu!

Lovely setting down a side lane off Flinders. Very helpful staff who were friendly and attentive. However be prepared to pay $9 for one small scallop! Overall, the dishes were small and I left feeling hungry.

fields.name: Vegilicious
fields.information:
Vegilicious is a St. Kilda based vegetarian catering company with a diverse clientele ranging  from those based in the City of Port Phillip, to arts, music & community festivals throughout Melbourne and regional Victoria.
 
Vegilicious aims to raise awareness about eating for health, sustainability and care for the planet and its inhabitants, by providing alternate choices in food & encouraging arts to raise social consciousness, acting as agents of change that touch the broader community.
 
Vegilicious provides wholesome, organic, affordable vegetarian soul food, priding ourselves in serving super fresh food that is all homemade from scratch. All our produce is ethically sourced, considering locality, seasonality and environmental impact regarding packaging and waste.
 
Vegilicious' creator, Giovanna Ghelardini, affectionately known as Geo, was born into a wonderful Italian family. The love of home grown, seasonal food has always been paramount to Geo & the experience of working for 6 years as a kitchen garden specialist for the Stephanie Alexander Kitchen Garden Program has only added to the style of healthy, seasonal hearty cooking.
 
Running for 8 years now, we consistently provide delicious vegetarian food. Guaranteed super tasty, wholesome and very generous catering for all types of functions and traveling to numerous festivals and gatherings.
 
Sustainability, environment and respect for our mother earth is our underlying motivation and of course providing people with fresh, beautiful, healthy, hearty food at an affordable price.

We provide catering for all types of functions and travel to many different festivals and gatherings. Sustainability, enviroment and repect for our mother earth is our underlying motivation and of course providing people with tasty, fresh, beautiful, healthy, hearty food at an affordable price.

Great service!! Food was pretty good also, definitely try the prawn tacos and tequila. Writing this now after 3 shots and 1l corona.. soo pretty happy about most things but in all great vibe and good food.

amazing food...awesome ambience...great service...everything about this place is nice 
must try!!!!!!
table reservation highly recommended....!!!!

What a great place! I can't belive everything here is vegan! They have pretty much all the vegan things you could want! I tried the bambam which was delicious! I got the mixed one and some rice. I can't wait to come back and try more of the food here!!!

You guys changed my life. Staff are beautiful, food is glorious and the price is so bloody good. For a young family we can't pass up an affordable delicous meal with exceptional service.

wow !! I came here today on a groupon, $40 for a three course meal for two people. Food was AMAZING, probably the best vegan restaurant I have been to. Was so impressed with this place. It looks like an ugly cafeteria but the food is outstanding! 
Amazing vegan food. The mushroom and tofu claypot was so authentic and flavourful, not spicy. The fake pork in the sweet n sour was excellent, had some nice heat to it, and the fried eggplant with sirracha mayo was crunchy and as delicious as you'd hope, a bit spicy. 
The staff are friendly and the serving sizes are generous. Can't wait to return. :)

fields.name: Ichirin
fields.address: Shop 2, Corner Beasley Road & Dundee Street, Leeming, Melville, Perth, WA
fields.information:
Ichirin put high quality, incredibly fresh products (seafood above all) at the forefront of what they offer. The preparation is often minimal, meaning guests at this suave but cosy Japanese restaurant on Dundee Street get to enjoy the natural goodness of these carefully sourced items. That said, there’s certainly no shortage of complex culinary skill on show at Ichirin, and very, very few modern Japanese restaurants in Perth can match the level of freshness, quality and affordability managed here.
Ichirin’s bento boxes are the stuff of legend around Leeming, and you will not regret reaching for one. Still, this Dundee Street star (beside Melville Glades golf course) is a place you can delve a bit further into Japanese dining than most spots in Perth. Why not try scallop, king prawn and seafood wrapped sea urchin tempura? Or soft-boiled abalone with sweet liver miso sauce? Ichirin’s amazing omakase (degustation) sets can be tailored to suit any party size and are ideal for group dining

fields.name: G2 Korean BBQ
fields.information: G2 Korean BBQ gives you top quality meat and seafood (and a little guidance) to sizzle up to your liking, right at the table, over a hot grill.

fields.name: Pachi Pachi
fields.address: 608 Albany Highway, Victoria Park, Perth, WA
fields.information: PachiPachi is born out of love and passion for good honest food. We put together a menu of delights from the Far East to Down Under!

fields.name: Ria Malay Kitchen
fields.information: True to its word, Ria offers authentic home-style Malaysian cooking. Embracing all the cultural influences that have been added to the Malay melting pot over the years, the menu is a tantalizing fusion of flavours from Malaysia, India, China and even Portugal.

fields.name: Side Door BBQ
fields.information: Mouthwatering American Style BBQ, Fully Licensed in the heart of Mt Lawley.

fields.name: Chilli Orange
fields.address: 21 Angove St, North Perth, Perth, WA
fields.information: Serving a contemporary asian menu with an array of entrees to share and selection of mains, where asian food is revamped with a western influence. Our restaurant aims to create an intimate but professional atmosphere where you can enjoy top quality service in a relaxed environment. We ensure personal and efficient service.

fields.name: Sauma
fields.address: William Street Arcade, Northbridge, Perth, WA
fields.information: At the heart of enlivened, heritage Northbridge....Sauma adds a chicly rustic meeting place to Perth’s cultural precinct. Set facing the vibrant hub of a bright and animated community Sauma presents a modern Indian street-food experience – emphasising freshness, creativity and raw charm.

fields.name: Sister of Soul
fields.information:
Modern global vegetarian and vegan food and drinks that is clean, tasty and nourishing.

Reviews from Zomato:

Nice place for a brunch. I like the atmosphere although the staff is a bit cold. 
But the food is good and cofee and hot choccy are amazing !!

Just had the most disgusting and abusive encounter with a staff member of this restaurant during a visit. Shocking customer service. Avoid like the plague.

The service and area is lovely and the staff are so friendly and fantastic, always willing to cater to your every need. However, it's the food that lets this Acland Street restaurant down. The food is by no means awful, definitely edible but I've never had a fantastic meal here. The deserts on the other hand are great and I would definitely recommend popping in after dinner for the 'Not So Rocky Road
Veg heaven 💕
Paid a visit to St Kilda and was in need of something filling so the lovely waitress recommended the smashed pumpkin on toast! 
I opted for the almond feta to feed my curiosity - it doesn't taste like dairy feta but is still delicious! It definitely has a bit of bite to it which I liked. 
Coffees were good and they arrived quickly. 
We arrived super early in the morning so the cafe was nice and quiet but by the time we left it was definitely packed! 
Would be recommending this place to everyone, even those who aren't vegetarian/vegan.

fields.name: Trippy Taco
fields.information:
Trippy Taco is a Melbourne taco institution renowned for its affordable, street inspired ‘fresh mex’ where a healthy vegetarian cuisine takes centre stage, hand made tortillas are made fresh daily in-house, and gluten-free options are readily available. 

Fully licensed and offering a selection of Mexican beers, sangria and delicious cocktails, Trippy Taco is located in both Fitzroy’s iconic Gertrude St, and trendy Southside Acland St.

What makes your restaurant different? Trippy Taco has its own flavour, which has developed over the last decade. Our main focus is the food, and making it accessible to all. Although we don't use meat, I have never labelled Trippy Taco as vegetarian or even Mexican for that matter. I think the food stands on it's own.

What is your favourite meal on the menu, and why? My favourite is breakfast tacos. I always love the combination of eggs, salsa and fresh corn tortillas. It's a very light, fresh and satisfying way to start the day (with a glass of fresh OJ). I also find it difficult to go past our Original Tacos and of course Trippy Fries! 

What has been your proudest achievement to date? Probably seeing how happy and proud, relieved my parents and family were when I opened the new shop. Mum, Dad, Myself, as well as my good friend Sandy, pretty much did the entire shop fit out ourselves. They have really put in lots of hard work to get it off the ground!

fields.name: Six Willows Cafe
fields.address: 6/49 Rostrata Avenue, Willetton, Canning, Perth, WA
fields.information: Six Willows cafe is where our customers come to feel relaxed, bump into their neighbors and enjoy a good laugh. It is a cafe, a retail space of WA local artisan wares and a casual meeting spot.

fields.name: Harvest Espresso
fields.address: 629 Albany Highway, Victoria Park, Perth, WA
fields.information: Harvest Espresso is owned by an experienced husband & wife who lead a passionate team of staff. We feature fresh seasonal dishes created with care, friendly professional service & reasonable prices.
